@node "Intro" "How a story begun"

  Once upon the time...

 Well, once I visited the Computer Room of our student hostels to find ANY
interesting in PeeCees.  Nothing, of course...  :) Except, that everybody
played with three games: C&C (really great game, that's true),
                         a silly game with spiders
                         and an even sillier gambling game!

 "@{i}Wow!@{ui}"- I said -"@{i}I have to write one of those games!@{ui}"- so I looked those
three carefully. C&C is more over my genie, that should be a later plan! :)
The another "spiderized" game is still nice, but I had no time to know out
that one. (May be later!)
 And what about that gambling game? Ray traced animation, and nothing else.
"@{i}That's it!!@{ui}"- I shouted.
 "@{i}Traced!  Boring!  Easy-2-write!  Big-&-nothing-special!  Exact PeeCee
game!!!!@{ui}" ;)

 Then I discovered E! One of the greatest languages on Amiga. I learned it
completely under a week, an other week and it is ready!

 @{i}@{fg shine}Shells!@{ui}@{fg text} aproaches to the World! (On @{b}Aminet@{ub}...)

 About the animation:

 It consists of 65 frames, each frame needed @{i}50 min@{ui} to trace on my stock
A1200. :-P
 And after the convertation! I used @{b}Image Studio v1.1.0@{ub}, it @{i}does not have
Arexx interface@{ui}, I had to convert all frame by @{i}myself@{ui}... :-P again!

 Sorry about no sounds at all. I did not want to run out of 2 Megs.

                                  @{fg shine}@{i}Have fun!@{fg text}@{ui}

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Well, you will need at least a CyberStorm! :)"

 @{i}So, what do you really need?@{ui}

 Nothing special, but a stock@{i} @{fg shine}A1200 with HDD@{ui}@{fg text}. Or if you prefer:
@{fg shine}AGA chpiset@{fg text}, @{fg shine}KickStart 3.0@{fg text} and @{fg shine}2 Megs of any memory@{fg text}, but @{i}@{fg shine}no 68020 needed@{ui}@{fg text},
because the player not optimized on this way. It should run on every machine
with this features.

 First I thoght, I write routines to handle floppy disks, but finally I see
no reason, why anybody wanted to run this from floppy. It is not as good as
it worth to waste two disks.

 Buy HDD!

 I almost forgot: You may need a @{i}@{fg shine}PAL@{ui}@{fg text} machine. (I can't believe, anybody from
the USA is interested in this! :) )

@endnode

