@node "Using" "Easy-to-use is always suspicious!"

 It is really easy. When you start the program, -I hope I should not tell
you, how to start it, we are not PeeCee users, - it opens a window with three
gadgets on it. 
 @{fg shine}Level@{fg text} is the level of hardness, (three levels: @{i}Novice@{ui}, @{i}Advanced@{ui} and @{i}Expert@{ui}),
 @{fg shine}Start@{fg text} gadget starts the game,
 @{fg shine}Quit@{fg text} gadget quits from the program.

 You can select from menu the showing of top list, and about box.

 Now, if you start the game, then @{i}three traced shells@{ui} appear on the screen.
One of them will lift up, and show you a @{i}red ball@{ui} under. Then the program
begins to @{i}shuffle@{ui} those tree shells, and after "some" changing, you have
to guess, which shell @{i}contains@{ui} the ball.
 It is an easy game, everybody knows it. If you fail, then the game is over.
If you get enough score, you can type your name into a reqester, and you can
check on the list of @{i}Big Shellers@{ui}. (Separated for each level of course!)

 Ok. @{i}@{fg shine}Now stop dogging around, lets play!@{fg text}@{ui}
@endnode

